FIND
	To search for files and directories
Find    /      -name        <file-name>
Find    /home     -name        <file-name>
Find    /etc     -name        <file-name>
Find    /Desktop     -name        <file-name>
Find /home -name <file-name>  --------- specific search for file
Find /  -type f -name "*.log"   ----------- by extension
Find .  -name <file-name> ----------------current  directory operation
 Find by name

find /   home -name "file.txt"

Find by type

find / -type f      --------- files
find / -type d      -----------directories

 Find by size

find /var -size +100M       -------------greater than 100MB
find /var -size -10M        ------------less than 10MB
find /var -size 50M       ---------------exactly 50MB

Find by permissions

find / -perm 777
find / -perm -u=rwx

Find by user

find /home -user ec2-user

Find by modified time

find / -mtime 1     -------------modified 1 day ago
find / -mtime -1    --------------modified in last 24 hrs
find / -mtime +7     --------------older than 7 days

 Find and delete files

find /tmp -name "*.log" -delete

Find empty files

find / -type f -empty

 Find large files (useful for disk cleanup)

find / -type f -size +500M
Option
Meaning
-mtime
File modified time (content changed)
-atime
File access time (opened/read)
-ctime
File change time (permissions/owner changed)

Symbol
Meaning
-
less than (recent)
+
more than (older)
no sign
exact

find .   -type f  -newermt    "2026-04-10 10:00:00"

LOCATE
     - To quickly find files by name.
Sudo updatedb --------------settings for the file
Locate <file_name> -------------- faster than find

Limit results

locate -n 5 file.txt

Match exact filename

locate -r "/file.txt$"

